
[1]deformity

   DEFORMITY, n.

   1. Any unnatural state of the shape or form; want of that uniformity or
   symmetry which constitutes beauty; distortion; irregularity of shape or
   features; disproportion of limbs; defect; crookedness, &c. Hence,
   ugliness; as bodily deformity.

   2. Any thing that destroys beauty, grace or propriety; irregularity;
   absurdity; gross deviation from order, or the established laws of
   propriety. Thus we speak of deformity in an edifice, or deformity of
   character.
